{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01LiGKUHMdPcm3RsGsVPS1ZD","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I see the issue. In `new_var`, when `comp_is_named_gbl(parser->vm)` is true:\n```c\nif (comp_is_named_gbl(parser->vm)) {\n    /* change to ETNGLBAL */\n    bexpdesc key;\n    init_exp(&key, ETSTRING, 0);\n    key.v.s = name;\n    init_exp(var, ETNGLOBAL, 0);\n\n\n```\n\nI'm calling `be_code_nglobal` to allocate a register for the key string, and storing that register index in `var->v.idx`. So when `comp_is_named_gbl` is true, `e` becomes ETNGLOBAL with an index pointing to the register holding the name string. Then in `class_static_assignment_expr`, I copy the class description and prepare to call `be_code_member`.\n\nIn `package_suffix`, I'm converting both the key and the class object to registers using `exp2anyreg`, which for ETNGLOBAL types means loading the named global into a new register. Now I'm checking whether those temporary registers get freed after `class_static_assignment_expr` completes, looking at the `free_suffix` function to see how suffix registers are released.\n\nThe `e->v.ss.tt` field stores the original type of the object before it was converted to ETMEMBER, so if the object was originally ETNGLOBAL, that's what gets preserved there.\n\nWhen `e` is ETNGLOBAL, the condition `e->v.ss.tt == ETREG` evaluates to false, which means the register allocated by `exp2anyreg` in `package_suffix` never gets freed. This causes a register leak in each iteration of the loop—the class variable keeps consuming registers without releasing them, eventually leading to overflow.\n\nLet me trace through `package_suffix` more carefully. The function calls `exp2anyreg` on the class variable, which converts it from ETNGLOBAL to ETREG and allocates a register. Then it saves the type as `c->v.ss.tt = c->type`, which would be ETREG at that point. So actually, the saved type should be ETREG, not ETN